Introduced Version
SENATE BILL No. 82
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 35-47-11.1-4.
Synopsis: Local regulation of firearms in Marion County. Provides
that certain restrictions on the local regulation of firearms, ammunition,
and firearm accessories may not be construed to prevent a county
containing a consolidated city from regulating firearms, ammunition,
or firearm accessories in a manner more restrictive than Indiana law if
the regulation is recommended by a law enforcement agency that has
jurisdiction in the county. Specifies regulations that meet these
parameters. Requires compliance with the federal and state
constitutions.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Qaddoura
December 8, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Corrections and Criminal
Law.
